I"å	<h1 id="cosmology-textbooks">Cosmology Textbooks</h1>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Introduction-Cosmology-Barbara-Ryden/dp/1107154839/ref=sr_1_3?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1539634625&amp;sr=8-3&amp;keywords=introduction+to+cosmology">Introduction to Cosmology</a> by Barbara Ryden: Good introduction book, containing basic topics. But this book lacks some detailed calculations.</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Galaxy-Formation-Evolution-Houjun-Mo/dp/0521857937/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1539634728&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=galaxy+formation">Galaxy Formation and Evolution</a> by Houjun Mo, Frank van den Bosch and Simon White: Bible of Cosmology and Galaxy Evolution. It contains everything you want.</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Principles-Physical-Cosmology-Phillip-Peebles/dp/0691074283/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1539634841&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=physical+cosmology">Principles of Physical Cosmology</a> by Peebles: This is more like a reference book, and may be out-of-date.</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Cosmological-Physics-Cambridge-Astrophysics-Peacock-ebook/dp/B00INYGDII/ref=sr_1_2?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1539634953&amp;sr=8-2&amp;keywords=cosmology+peacock">Cosmological Physics</a> by Peacock: Very complicated and hard to understand, but Yingjie said itâ€™s worth reading.</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Observational-Cosmology-Stephen-Serjeant/dp/0521157153/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1539635005&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=observational+cosmology">Observational Cosmology</a> by Stephen Serjeant: A very very good textbook on observational cosmology! Definitely worth reading!</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Cosmology-Steven-Weinberg/dp/0198526822/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1539635176&amp;sr=8-1&amp;keywords=cosmology+weinberg">Cosmology</a> by Weinberg: Theoretical physicistâ€™s approach.</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.springer.com/us/book/9783319955698">Lecture notes on cosmology</a> by Oliver Piattella: A good lecture notes for graduate cosmology. I like the miscellaneous part of this book which talks about supernova cosmology. This lecture notes can also be downloaded from <a href="http://ofp.cosmo-ufes.org/uploads/1/3/7/0/13701821/cosmology-ln.pdf">here</a>.</li>
  <li><a href="http://www.lsst-desc.org/DEschool">LSST Dark Energy School</a></li>
